condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2Section I.E.1 | Description :Upon the selection of any works (a) carry out an environmental/socialassessment, and approve EMP or similar for each work; and (b)implement said EMP | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2Section I.E.2 | Description :If Resettlement is involved, (a) prior to the carrying out of any saidworks, prepare and furnish to the Bank, a resettlement plan; and (b) implement said plan. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2Section I.E.3 | Description :If Indigenous Peoples are involved, (a) prior to the carrying out of anysaid works, prepare and furnish to the Bank, an IPP; and (b) implement said plan. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2Section II.B.4 | Description :Prior to the commencement of each calendar year, create, and maintain aspecific budget line entry in the national annual budget (starting in CY2011) to keep track of Project expenditures. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2Section IV.B.1 (b) | Description :No withdrawal shall be made for: ... (b) under category (1) (Worksunder Subprojects) unless: (i) at least one of the Participating Provinces has entered into a PTA | Due Date :02-May-2011

title.narrative: Number of people in the NGR that benefits from urban drainage networks built under the Project
Number of people in urban areas provided with access to Improved Water Sources under the project
Number of water providers that have implemented a monitoring system (management panel) as a tool for strategic decision making to improve management.
New piped household water connections that are resulting from the project intervention
Number of more efficient and financially healthier providers of WSS services
Number of piped households that receive safe water treated according to regulatory standards
Evidence that at least 30% percent of additional beneficiaries of the new water supply infrastructure built under the Project are poor
Number of service providers at the provincial or municipal level enrolled in an institutional development program financed by the Project
Surface of urban area protected from flooding with drainage networks built under the project
Disperse indigenous population with improved access to water from the works built under the project
